    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "@Ankur Creating the collection view is just creating object wrappers and setting up some links, so it&#39;s <code>O(1)</code>. Then, as it&#39;s a <i>view</i> (i.e. not a copy of the actual entries), fetching each entry via <code>iterator.next()</code> might have some hidden costs. In the case of <code>TreeMap</code>, I think it would need to reach the lowest entry, i.e. the leftmost leaf of the tree, which would be <code>O(logN)</code> because the tree is balanced. Then, for the rest of the entries, it would be just a red-black tree traversal, which would yield <code>O(1)</code> for each fetched entry, totalling <code>logN + N - 1 ~ O(N)</code> for the whole traversal."
  }, {
