  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/53670535/treemap-collection-views-iterators-time-complexity",
  "title" : "TreeMap collection views iterators time-complexity?",
  "body" : "<p>Time-complexity of all 3 collection view iterators for <code>HashMap</code> (<code>myHashMap.entrySet().iterator().next()</code> and <code>myHashMap.keySet().iterator().next()</code> and <code>myHashMap.values().iterator().next()</code>) is well-documented in Javadoc, it is <em>O(n+c)</em> for all those 3 iterators (n is number of mappings, c is capacity that is physical number of buckets in hashtable).</p>\n<p>But what about respective 3 iterators of 3 respective <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/25/docs/api//java.base/java/util/TreeMap.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>TreeMap</code></a> collection views? Nothing is said in official Javadoc. What are their complexities? I did look in SE8 source code but I cannot judge from there.</p>\n"
